Maintainer: Wenxuan Liu <wenxuan.liu@ucdconnect.ie>
Description: Metabolomics is the measurement of metabolites in biological samples 
        to reveal information on metabolic pathways and phenotypes. 
        It provides a framework to perform soft clustering using 
        simplex-structured matrix factorisation (SSMF). It contains a set of functions
        for determining the optimal number of prototypes, the optimal algorithmic
        parameters, the estimation confidence intervals and the diversity of clusters.
        Abdolali, Maryam & Gillis, Nicolas (2020) <doi:10.1137/20M1354982>.
        Tibshirani, R., Walther, G., & Hastie, T (2001) <doi:10.1111/1467-9868.00293>.
        Stine, R (1989) <doi:10.1177/0049124189018002003>.
        Flynt, A., Dean, N. & Nugent, R (2019) <doi:10.1007/s11634-018-0346-x>.
